<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Spelling Beez Would
   Never Be the Same
</HL>
<DATE>
08/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<LP>
   Amity Shlaes's (Shlaziz) ardikl about the French chrying 2
rerite ther langwidge n 2 spelling wurdz egzakli lik tha soun
seemz lik a gud idea (editorial page, Joon 27). Jus think,
awl children hoo lurn 2 reed an spel fonetikli kud pronouns
an spel nyeerli inny wurd tha c without evn noing hwot it
meenz. Awlso, ther wud b fyew argyumints or gisadreemints (I
meen disagreemintz) kunserning how a wurd iz pronounsd or
speld.
   Anuthr idea iz 2 develup a kod that nonfonik tip peepl kud
not komprehin. That iz, revurs leterz or silabls from wun
wurd to anuthr n yur sintens. For egzampl, this paragraf's
furst sintens wud reed: Inuthr adea iz 2 kevelup a dod that
fon-nonic pip teepl nud kot pomkrehin. B kairfl tho bkawz u
mit kreat sum awf kulr fraziz an sounz. I don't no if enuf
peepl wud do this but it kan kreat sum inchresting sounz and
wurdz (or wounz and surdz).
</LP>
<TEXT>
